 instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Wettenhall was born about 1218. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Matthew de Domville."},"et":{"Circa 1218–":"umbes 1218–Surnud","1214–Male":"1214–Surnud","1239–1289":"1239–1289","–Female":"Surnud","1218–Female":"1218–Surnud","1239":"1239","1214":"1214","about 1239":"umbes 1239","1289":"1289","Circa 1218":"umbes 1218","1218":"1218","Oxton, Cheshire, England":"Oxton, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"Circa 1218–":"noin 1218–Kuollut","1214–Male":"1214–Kuollut","1239–1289":"1239–1289","–Female":"Kuollut","1218–Female":"1218–Kuollut","1239":"1239","1214":"1214","about 1239":"noin 1239","1289":"1289","Circa 1218":"noin 1218","1218":"1218","Oxton, Cheshire, England":"Oxton, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"Circa 1218–":"environ 1218–Décédée","1214–Male":"1214–Décédé","1239–1289":"1239–1289","–Female":"Décédée","1218–Female":"1218–Décédée","1239":"1239","1214":"1214","about 1239":"environ 1239","1289":"1289","Circa 1218":"environ 1218","1218":"1218","Oxton, Cheshire, England":"Oxton, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Agnes Wettenhall est née environ 1218. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Matthew de Domville."},"de":{"Circa 1218–":"um 1218–Verstorben","1214–Male":"1214–Verstorben","1239–1289":"1239–1289","–Female":"Verstorben","1218–Female":"1218–Verstorben","1239":"1239","1214":"1214","about 1239":"um 1239","1289":"1289","Circa 1218":"um 1218","1218":"1218","Oxton, Cheshire, England":"Oxton, Cheshire, England","l